Difference between document and window object

Document object: 
(i) The document object represent a web page that is loaded in the browser.
(ii) The document object can be accessed with a window.document or just document.
(iii) The document object represents the whole html document as a tree of Objects(HTML, HEAD, BODY, and other HTML tags).

Syntax:
document.property_name;

Window Object: 
(i) The window object is the topmost object of the DOM hierarchy. 
(ii) It represents a browser window or frame that displays the contents of the webpage.
(iii) The window object has many useful properties like the location object and the setTimeout function.

Syntax:
window.property_name;


